HEADWORD: Truckle-bed
<hw>Truc"kle-bed`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A low bed on
wheels, that may be pushed under another bed; a trundle-bed.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧His standing bed and <xex>truckle-bed</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

